[[Doctor of Philosophy]] in [[Art History]], '''Fabien Danesi''' is a [[lecturer]] in theory and practice of [[photography]] at the Faculty of Arts of the [[University of Picardie Jules Verne]] in [[Amiens]].<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.vivoequidem.net/galerie/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=579%3Aart-et-sf-texte-de-valerie-mavridorakis-et-fabien-danesi&catid=250%3Aarticles&Itemid=645&lang=fr ART ET SCIENCE-FICTION, La Ballard connection Entretien entre Valérie Mavridorakis et Fabien Danesi]</ref><ref>{{fr}}] [http://www.cotecaen.fr/tag/fabien-danesi/ Une conférence sur l'art des années 60, à Caen]</ref> Former resident of the [[Villa Medici]],<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.villamedici.it/fr/resident/39/danesi/?of=44&t=historien-de-l-art Fabien Danesi]</ref> [[French Academy in Rome]] in 2007–2008,<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.lespressesdureel.com/auteur.php?id=442 Fabien Danesi]</ref> he previously taught at the [[François Rabelais University]] of [[Tours]], [[Paris 13 University]], [[Pantheon-Sorbonne University]] and the [[Versailles Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines University]].<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.inha.fr/spip.php?article2673 Fabien Danesi, chercheur accueilli Fondation de France]</ref><ref>{{fr}}[http://www.paris-art.com/editeur-design/l-Œil-nomade-la-photographie-de-voyage-avec-ange-leccia/danesi-fabien/1233.html L'auteur Fabien Danesi]</ref> Member of AICA-France (''Association Internationale des Critiques d'Art'', in English International Association of Art Critics), he regularly collaborates with the ''Pavilion Neuflize OBC'', laboratory creation which annually hosts ten young artists and curators recruited after an international competition from over 300 applications of the ''[[Palais de Tokyo]]''.
